"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939916","Department for Transport","false","2018-07-17","<p>£87,706 was spent on London buses in respect of the London North Eastern Railway (LNER) brand awareness campaign which was commissioned prior to 24 June 2018.</p><p> </p><p>The East Coast mainline continues to generate operating profits and LNER pays money into the public purse.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-07-17T15:57:40.407Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939916/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939916/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939916/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-07-12","London North Eastern Railway","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much funding has been allocated from the public purse for advertising the LNER service on London buses.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","163590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939917","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-07-18","<p>A cross-Departmental steering group has been established to oversee the work to develop options for a UK GNSS. The steering group comprises 11 officials from the UK Space Agency, the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, the Ministry of Defence, the Cabinet Office, the Foreign and Commonwealth Office and the Infrastructure and Projects Authority.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-07-18T08:41:09.133Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939917/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939917/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939917/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-07-12","Galileo System","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Environment and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister for Defence Procurement of 9 July 2018, on Leaving the EU: Defence and Military Aerospace Industry, Official Report, column 694, how many civil servants are part of the cross-departmental group; and from which departments those civil servants are drawn.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","163529"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939918","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-07-17","<p>The Combat Air Strategy, which the Secretary of State for Defence announced on 21 February 2018 to the Defence Committee, was published on 16 July 2018.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-07-17T15:26:09.037Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939918/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939918/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939918/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-07-12","Military Aircraft: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister for Defence Procurement of 9 July 2018, on Leaving the EU: Defence and Military Aerospace Industry, Official Report, column 694, when his Department plans to publish the Future Combat Air Strategy.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","163530"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939919","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-07-17","<p>In developing the Combat Air Strategy, Ministry of Defence officials have held discussions with a range of European nations, as well as a number of allies and partners from across the globe.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-07-17T15:20:11.873Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939919/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939919/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/939919/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-07-12","Military Aircraft: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister for Defence Procurement of 9 July 2018, on Leaving the EU: Defence and Military Aerospace Industry, Official Report, column 694, which European countries are working with the UK on the Future Combat Air Strategy.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","163531"
