"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/940020","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-07-18","<p>We have raised the case of Hasan Mushaima at a senior level. The UK encourages those with concerns about treatment in detention to report these to the relevant human rights oversight bodies. We urge those bodies to carry out swift and thorough investigations. The UK continues to encourage the Government of Bahrain to deliver on its international and domestic human rights commitments.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-07-18T15:39:38.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/940020/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/940020/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/940020/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-07-12","Hassan Mushaima","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations have been made to the Government of Bahrain on the denial of access to adequate medical treatment of imprisoned Bahraini political leader Hassan Mushaima.","false","Biography information for Karen Lee","Lincoln","Karen Lee","163627"
